text: Miranda's snouted tree frog, fuscous-blotched tree frog, snouted tree frog, or San Luis snouted tree frog (Scinax fuscovarius) is a frog that lives in Argentina, Brazil, and Paraguay. Scientists have seen it between and 150 and 1800 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax fuscovarius
